      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BAROOGA JIM (6) has some solid form under his belt and proved too strong last time to win by 4.5 lengths at this track in a handy 34.47 beating Melvin Bale. Winner at his latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Makes plenty of appeal on the back of that last-start win. URANA XAVIER (1) has a strong record this journey here with four wins and a minor from nine starts. Placed last time (34.60) at The Meadows in a Free For All, finishing third and beaten 2 lengths. Looks suited here and can measure up. DEADLY COOL (4) is better than last start when seventh (30.11) in a Special conditions H at this track over 515m. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Shapes as one to consider. GOLD CODE (2) was well fancied last time on the back of some sparkling form, which included a two-start winning streak, but could only manage second (32.51) at Traralgon. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors.",
